1
00:00:03,379 --> 00:00:05,632
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,715 --> 00:00:08,343
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,426 --> 00:00:13,515
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,598 --> 00:00:18,686
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:26,986 --> 00:00:31,282
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:33,284
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:33,368 --> 00:00:39,874
<i>The dream info real/Ty</i>

8
00:00:42,627 --> 00:00:48,466
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,550 --> 00:00:51,928
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,595 --> 00:00:54,889
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,973 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:02,564
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,902
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,069 --> 00:01:11,489
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,531 --> 00:01:17,245
<i>World.</i>

16
00:01:26,462 --> 00:01:30,508
The human whose name is written
in this note shall die.

17
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:33,803
Please...

18
00:01:34,137 --> 00:01:35,471
<i>- Stop!
- Now lefis see...</i>

19
00:01:35,471 --> 00:01:36,264
TAKUO SHIBUIMARU
ACCIDENTAL DEATH

20
00:01:36,264 --> 00:01:36,556
<i>What will happen!</i>

21
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:41,811
<i>The Death Note is real!</i>

22
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:49,694
Don't think for a moment,

23
00:01:50,028 --> 00:01:53,197
that any human who's used
the Death Note can go to Heaven or Hell.

24
00:01:53,781 --> 00:01:56,868
I want the world to know...
of my existence!

25
00:01:57,493 --> 00:02:00,079
And that there's someone who is
passing judgment onto them!

26
00:02:00,663 --> 00:02:02,248
And I will become...

27
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:05,084
the god of this new world!

28
00:02:05,501 --> 00:02:08,421
CONFRONTATION

29
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:15,136
I had no idea what he was thinking,
so I'm done with him.

30
00:02:15,219 --> 00:02:18,306
Really? Then how was it
with that other older guy?

31
00:02:18,389 --> 00:02:19,849
Mr. Yagami.

32
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:22,435
Please translate the sentence
into Japanese.

33
00:02:22,644 --> 00:02:23,686
Yes.

34
00:02:26,689 --> 00:02:29,525
"When finally, he fully succeeded
in making his dream a reality,

35
00:02:29,609 --> 00:02:34,405
he was immersed in beatitude."

36
00:02:35,448 --> 00:02:36,616
Very good.

37
00:02:36,949 --> 00:02:40,578
As usual, a perfect answer.

38
00:02:44,082 --> 00:02:46,751
Well then, class is dismissed.

39
00:02:52,715 --> 00:02:54,592
- It's finally over.
- Where do you want to go after?

40
00:02:54,884 --> 00:02:57,095
- School sure is boring.
- Hmm, where should we go?

41
00:02:57,887 --> 00:02:58,888
Hey, Light!

42
00:02:59,597 --> 00:03:01,432
Light, are you listening to me?

43
00:03:01,724 --> 00:03:02,892
Don't talk to me.

44
00:03:03,393 --> 00:03:06,604
Others can hear my voice
when I talk, unlike yours.

45
00:03:07,021 --> 00:03:08,690
You're so boring.

46
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:11,317
Hey, Light! We're going to go...

47
00:03:11,401 --> 00:03:12,985
Sorry, I have something to do.

48
00:03:14,487 --> 00:03:16,197
You don't have anything to do.

49
00:03:16,489 --> 00:03:19,200
Aren't you just going home
like you usually do?

50
00:03:19,784 --> 00:03:21,911
What are you talking about?
I have something to do.

51
00:03:22,829 --> 00:03:25,665
Something very important.

52
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:29,961
<i>Yamada is suspected of stabbing
a fellow employee in the abdomen</i>

53
00:03:30,044 --> 00:03:32,672
<i>at a restaurant in Kabukicho,
Shinjuku, yesterday.</i>

54
00:03:32,755 --> 00:03:37,301
<i>The knife was from the restaurant
and was roughly twelve inches long.</i>

55
00:03:37,927 --> 00:03:38,970
<i>- Hey!
- The suspect said...</i>

56
00:03:39,053 --> 00:03:41,222
<i>- Hey, Ughfl
- "he was being rude, so I just lost it. "</i>

57
00:03:41,472 --> 00:03:42,557
What is it?

58
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:45,476
You're really working very hard.

59
00:03:45,768 --> 00:03:47,729
I can't waste any time.

60
00:03:48,563 --> 00:03:51,357
I only have a limited amount of time
to write names in the notebook...

61
00:03:52,024 --> 00:03:55,111
The only time I have is when I get
home from school and until I go to bed.

62
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:58,239
I also need to maintain my grades.

63
00:03:58,698 --> 00:04:00,283
I can't sleep during class.

64
00:04:00,992 --> 00:04:03,828
I need to do all of my homework
for school and my prep classes.

65
00:04:04,495 --> 00:04:06,164
Lack of sleep is dangerous.

66
00:04:06,622 --> 00:04:08,458
It will affect my health
and concentration.

67
00:04:09,125 --> 00:04:12,837
After all, I'm trying to change
this world into a utopia without evil.

68
00:04:13,087 --> 00:04:14,922
There's never enough time.

69
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:20,845
Why did you lock the door, Light?

70
00:04:21,387 --> 00:04:22,388
It's Sayu.

71
00:04:22,472 --> 00:04:23,639
What is it?

72
00:04:23,806 --> 00:04:25,266
Help me with my homework.

73
00:04:26,017 --> 00:04:27,769
Okay, sure.

74
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:33,191
It's on quadratic equations!

75
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:36,027
I'm sorry if you were studying.

76
00:04:36,486 --> 00:04:39,363
But it just doesn't make
any sense.

77
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:40,740
Please help me.

78
00:04:40,823 --> 00:04:41,824
All right.

79
00:04:41,949 --> 00:04:43,868
Light, be careful.

80
00:04:44,535 --> 00:04:47,789
Any human who touches
the notebook in your drawer...

81
00:04:47,872 --> 00:04:49,707
will be able to see me.

82
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:55,046
<i>He waits to tell me that
crucial detail now? Damn Shinigami!</i>

83
00:04:55,755 --> 00:04:57,215
What's wrong, Light?

84
00:04:57,298 --> 00:04:58,716
It's nothing.

85
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:01,969
Well, what exactly
don't you understand?

86
00:05:02,428 --> 00:05:04,138
Well, umm...

87
00:05:04,305 --> 00:05:05,389
I think everything.

88
00:05:06,516 --> 00:05:08,351
From what we know,

89
00:05:08,434 --> 00:05:09,936
there have been 52 deaths
just this past week.

90
00:05:10,353 --> 00:05:12,355
All from heart attacks.

91
00:05:12,688 --> 00:05:17,527
They're all criminals who were wanted
or being held in prison.

92
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:21,614
There are probably other criminals
whose deaths are still unaccounted for.

93
00:05:22,031 --> 00:05:24,408
Does that mean the death toll
could easily be over a hundred?

94
00:05:28,579 --> 00:05:30,790
Chief. . .we've already started!

95
00:05:31,123 --> 00:05:34,001
I know.
I had a call from headquarters.

96
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:35,670
At any rate...

97
00:05:35,753 --> 00:05:38,548
they were all criminals who
probably would have been executed.

98
00:05:38,631 --> 00:05:40,341
Perhaps we shouldn't
concern ourselves...

99
00:05:40,424 --> 00:05:41,425
Are you stupid?!

100
00:05:41,717 --> 00:05:43,928
It doesn't matter if
they're criminals or on death row.

101
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:45,263
Killing them is still murder.

102
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:48,015
We aren't even sure that
they were murdered.

103
00:05:48,474 --> 00:05:51,394
How can over 100 people
have heart attacks at the same time?!

104
00:05:51,894 --> 00:05:53,104
It has got to be murder.

105
00:05:53,604 --> 00:05:58,025
Is it even possible to kill
that many people at the same time?

106
00:05:58,234 --> 00:06:02,321
We believe that a large organization
carefully orchestrated these killings.

107
00:06:02,697 --> 00:06:04,782
If you say a large organization
is involved,

108
00:06:04,866 --> 00:06:08,119
I can't help but think that
the FBI or CIA is involved.

109
00:06:08,661 --> 00:06:09,954
I dare you to say that again!

110
00:06:10,037 --> 00:06:12,832
Now, now.
Let's stop joking around.

111
00:06:13,249 --> 00:06:15,835
We have to first clarify if these
are murders,

112
00:06:15,918 --> 00:06:17,211
or strange coincidences.

113
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:19,380
But don't all the autopsy reports
say that

114
00:06:19,463 --> 00:06:22,133
the deaths were caused
by inexplicable heart attacks?

115
00:06:22,425 --> 00:06:26,637
I don't see what else can be learned
from just the way they died.

116
00:06:26,888 --> 00:06:27,972
That's right!

117
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:30,892
It would be worth looking into
if they were stabbed with knives!

118
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:35,146
If that's the case,
we'll just have to have L solve this!

119
00:06:38,691 --> 00:06:40,192
What do you think?

120
00:06:42,528 --> 00:06:44,906
Chief, what is "L"?

121
00:06:45,114 --> 00:06:47,783
This is your first time at
this conference, isn't it?

122
00:06:48,534 --> 00:06:52,872
No one knows L's name, location
or what he looks like.

123
00:06:53,664 --> 00:06:55,833
But he's managed to solve
every case he's taken,

124
00:06:55,917 --> 00:06:57,585
no matter how difficult it is.

125
00:06:57,710 --> 00:07:00,671
He's cracked many of
the world's unsolved cases.

126
00:07:00,755 --> 00:07:02,632
He's our trump card,
our secret weapon.

127
00:07:02,924 --> 00:07:04,383
Our last hope.

128
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:05,718
Something like that.

129
00:07:06,802 --> 00:07:12,475
But isn't L so arrogant that he
only takes cases that interest him?

130
00:07:12,683 --> 00:07:13,684
That's right.

131
00:07:13,976 --> 00:07:16,562
We can't even contact him.

132
00:07:17,021 --> 00:07:18,856
I is already involved.

133
00:07:30,952 --> 00:07:34,580
I is already investigating this case.

134
00:07:34,956 --> 00:07:36,540
Huh? Watari?

135
00:07:36,624 --> 00:07:38,042
Watari?

136
00:07:38,334 --> 00:07:41,045
He's the only man who can contact L.

137
00:07:41,587 --> 00:07:44,340
Furthermore, Watari's identity
is also unknown...

138
00:07:44,757 --> 00:07:46,217
Please be silent.

139
00:07:46,676 --> 00:07:48,886
I will now speak.

140
00:07:53,307 --> 00:07:55,142
<i>Members of the ICPO...</i>

141
00:07:57,186 --> 00:07:58,229
<i>lam L.</i>

142
00:07:59,897 --> 00:08:04,986
What are we doing sneaking around
such a desolate place, Light?

143
00:08:05,695 --> 00:08:09,407
People who touch the Death Note
can see you, can't they?

144
00:08:10,074 --> 00:08:13,244
I can't walk around with
something this dangerous.

145
00:08:13,869 --> 00:08:16,747
Up until now, I thought that if
my family saw the notebook...

146
00:08:17,206 --> 00:08:20,126
I could pass it off as
a record of <i>cases</i>

147
00:08:20,209 --> 00:08:23,045
which I'm using to study
to become a detective.

148
00:08:23,629 --> 00:08:26,090
But I'm walking a fine line
right now.

149
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:27,842
If I'm not careful,

150
00:08:27,925 --> 00:08:29,468
I might end up killing...

151
00:08:30,094 --> 00:08:31,762
my own family.

152
00:08:39,687 --> 00:08:41,731
<i>This case is unprecedented
in scope and difficulty.</i>

153
00:08:41,814 --> 00:08:43,482
<i>It involves more people than
any other case preceding it.</i>

154
00:08:43,691 --> 00:08:48,863
<i>It is also an unforgivable case
of serial murder.</i>

155
00:08:49,822 --> 00:08:54,326
<i>In order to solve this case,
I need the ICPO...</i>

156
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:57,455
<i>no, various worldwide organizations,
to cooperate fully.</i>

157
00:08:57,538 --> 00:09:01,667
<i>I want you to decide whether
you'll support me at this conference.</i>

158
00:09:02,418 --> 00:09:07,006
<i>Also. . .I strongly desire to work
with the Japanese Police.</i>

159
00:09:07,965 --> 00:09:09,884
W-Why Japan?

160
00:09:10,634 --> 00:09:12,970
<i>Regardless of how many
suspects there are,</i>

161
00:09:13,262 --> 00:09:16,057
<i>there's a strong possibility
that they are Japanese.</i>

162
00:09:16,974 --> 00:09:19,810
<i>Even if they aren't Japanese,
they are hiding in Japan.</i>

163
00:09:20,352 --> 00:09:21,645
What grounds do you
have for your claims?

164
00:09:22,313 --> 00:09:24,148
<i>Why Japan?</i>

165
00:09:24,565 --> 00:09:28,652
<i>I think I can show you very soon
by directly confronting the perpetrator.</i>

166
00:09:29,737 --> 00:09:31,363
A direct confrontation?

167
00:09:31,947 --> 00:09:35,451
<i>At any rate, I would like set up
headquarters in Japan.</i>

168
00:09:41,373 --> 00:09:42,958
That was pretty easy to make...

169
00:09:43,459 --> 00:09:46,170
Hmm? Does that mean you
were able to hide the notebook?

170
00:09:46,629 --> 00:09:49,131
Yeah, in this drawer.

171
00:09:50,132 --> 00:09:52,343
Does that count as a hiding place?

172
00:09:53,302 --> 00:09:55,012
You left the key in the lock.

173
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:56,305
That's fine.

174
00:09:57,139 --> 00:10:00,392
It's better that I intentionally
left the key in a noticeable place.

175
00:10:03,312 --> 00:10:05,064
That's just a regular diary!

176
00:10:05,523 --> 00:10:09,860
Most people will probably be satisfied
with the secrets of this drawer...

177
00:10:09,944 --> 00:10:12,238
after reading this diary.

178
00:10:12,571 --> 00:10:13,697
But...

179
00:10:13,781 --> 00:10:16,033
The real key...is this.

180
00:10:16,826 --> 00:10:20,371
There's nothing suspicious
about having one of these on my desk.

181
00:10:20,454 --> 00:10:21,789
It's just a regular ballpoint pen.

182
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:23,207
I'll use the ink cartridge.

183
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:25,042
That's the key?

184
00:10:25,584 --> 00:10:27,670
Yeah. On the back of the drawer...

185
00:10:27,753 --> 00:10:30,297
there's a small hole that's hard
to notice if you don't look closely.

186
00:10:31,006 --> 00:10:32,633
You put this in the hole.

187
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:39,723
I see.
It's got a false bottom.

188
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:43,936
Well, you also have the fake diary,
so I doubt anyone will find it.

189
00:10:44,353 --> 00:10:45,437
That's not all.

190
00:10:46,647 --> 00:10:49,358
Even if they discovered
it has a false bottom,

191
00:10:49,525 --> 00:10:52,236
there would be no way that
they could take the notebook.

192
00:10:54,196 --> 00:10:55,239
You see...

193
00:10:55,531 --> 00:10:59,326
This ink cartridge is an insulator
so it doesn't channel electricity,

194
00:10:59,410 --> 00:11:01,120
and stops the flow of electricity
in the circuit.

195
00:11:01,579 --> 00:11:03,205
When the bottom of
this drawer is closed,

196
00:11:03,289 --> 00:11:06,542
this piece of rubber also
stops the flow of electricity.

197
00:11:06,709 --> 00:11:10,421
However, if someone were to
force open the bottom,

198
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:14,592
gasoline in thin plastic bags
will ignite at that moment and...

199
00:11:16,427 --> 00:11:18,345
the notebook will instantly
be set aflame.

200
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:20,681
All evidence will be
completely destroyed.

201
00:11:20,848 --> 00:11:22,057
That's how it's set up.

202
00:11:23,851 --> 00:11:25,060
I can just say the reason
I set it up to burn was that,

203
00:11:25,144 --> 00:11:28,898
"I didn't want anyone to
see my real diary."

204
00:11:28,981 --> 00:11:31,233
It's a believable excuse.

205
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:32,943
It/ls a notebook, after all.

206
00:11:34,278 --> 00:11:36,405
I've heard when a human
gets a Death Note,

207
00:11:36,655 --> 00:11:40,284
the biggest problem they have is
finding a good place to hide it.

208
00:11:40,743 --> 00:11:44,788
But Light, you're probably
the first to go this far.

209
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:47,917
But that setup is really dangerous.

210
00:11:48,584 --> 00:11:50,377
If you make
the slightest mistake,

211
00:11:50,461 --> 00:11:52,296
you could be badly burned.

212
00:11:52,922 --> 00:11:55,799
Dangerous?
You're talking nonsense again, Ryuk.

213
00:11:56,842 --> 00:11:59,553
I've been putting myself
in danger from the very beginning.

214
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:02,097
Ever since I first got a hold
of the Death Note.

215
00:12:03,057 --> 00:12:06,185
Compared to that,
this is hardly dangerous.

216
00:12:06,936 --> 00:12:09,313
In fact, quite the opposite.
It protects me.

217
00:12:10,522 --> 00:12:11,815
Which is better?

218
00:12:11,899 --> 00:12:14,944
A small fire in the house,
or being executed?

219
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:29,541
<i>Last night, within
the Tokyo West Penitentiary,</i>

220
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:34,797
<i>Naoki Kurotsukayama, aged thirty-two,
who was being detained for armed robbery...</i>

221
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,007
<i>is reported to have
died of a heart attack.</i>

222
00:12:37,383 --> 00:12:41,303
<i>In response to the endless,
bizarre deaths of prisoners...</i>

223
00:12:41,512 --> 00:12:43,973
That's amazing...
Bad guys just keep dying.

224
00:12:44,348 --> 00:12:46,684
It's a little scary,
but it does feel great.

225
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:48,602
But we really can't
do anything bad now.

226
00:12:48,936 --> 00:12:50,854
I wonder if the police are behind it.

227
00:12:51,188 --> 00:12:53,148
The police don't have
that kind of power.

228
00:12:53,315 --> 00:12:54,358
Don't you know about him?

229
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:55,651
Huh? About who?

230
00:12:56,402 --> 00:12:58,070
It's Kira... Kira!

231
00:12:58,779 --> 00:13:00,781
I wonder who's going
to be killed next...

232
00:13:01,031 --> 00:13:03,534
KIRA, KILL EVERYONE

233
00:13:04,034 --> 00:13:05,160
SEND MESSAGE?
SEND

234
00:13:06,203 --> 00:13:08,914
NAME: ROCOCO KIRA, KILL
EVERYONE NAME: MISERY

235
00:13:08,914 --> 00:13:09,415
Hmm?

236
00:13:09,748 --> 00:13:11,917
Someone's already created a website.

237
00:13:14,003 --> 00:13:15,879
"The legend of Kira the savior."

238
00:13:16,088 --> 00:13:18,966
That's pretty cool.
Is this about you?

239
00:13:19,341 --> 00:13:23,053
Yeah. "Kira" seems to come from
the English word "killer."

240
00:13:23,429 --> 00:13:24,805
I don't like it too much, but...

241
00:13:25,472 --> 00:13:28,267
I've become "Kira" to the world.

242
00:13:28,934 --> 00:13:32,855
Just searching the word "Kira," and
countless sites like this one appear.

243
00:13:33,731 --> 00:13:35,482
Television and newspapers have
only publicized

244
00:13:35,566 --> 00:13:39,445
"the successive, mysterious deaths
of vicious criminals."

245
00:13:40,195 --> 00:13:43,657
But the people of the world
can already feel it.

246
